  "prompt": "How can I format my memory card using cmd?",
  "response": "To format a memory card using the Command Prompt (CMD), follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Command Prompt as an administrator:\n   - Press Windows key + X\n   - Select \"Command Prompt (Admin)\" or \"Windows PowerShell (Admin)\"\n\n2. List available drives:\n   - Type `diskpart`\n   - Type `list disk`\n\n3. Select the memory card:\n   - Type `select disk X` (replace X with the disk number of your memory card)\n\n4. Format the memory card:\n   Option 1 (Quick Format):\n   - Type `format X: /fs:FAT32 /q` (for FAT32)\n   - Or `format X: /fs:exFAT /q` (for exFAT)\n\n   Option 2 (Full Format):\n   - Type `format X: /fs:FAT32` (for FAT32)\n   - Or `format X: /fs:exFAT` (for exFAT)\n\n5. Type `Y` to confirm\n\nNote:\n- Replace X with your memory card's drive letter\n- Choose FAT32 for cards \u226432GB\n- Choose exFAT for cards >32GB\n- Full format takes longer but more thoroughly erases data\n\nAlways backup important data before formatting.",
